(% style=&amp;#34;margin-bottom: 0in&amp;#34; %)
(% style=&amp;#34;font-family:Calibri;&amp;#34; %)**The United States federal government should provide a tax credit for tertiary recovery that uses industrial carbon dioxide.**

(% align=&amp;#34;CENTER&amp;#34; style=&amp;#34;margin-top: 0.33in; margin-bottom: 0in; border: 2.50pt solid #000000; padding: 0.01in 0.06in; page-break-inside: avoid; page-break-before: always; page-break-after: avoid&amp;#34; %)
(% style=&amp;#34;font-family: Calibri; font-size: 1.6em&amp;#34; %)**Adv 1 – CCS**

(% style=&amp;#34;margin-bottom: 0in&amp;#34; %)


(% style=&amp;#34;margin-bottom: 0in&amp;#34; %)
(% style=&amp;#34;font-family: Calibri; font-size: 0.8em&amp;#34; %)**Advantage 1 – Carbon Capture and Storage**

(% style=&amp;#34;margin-bottom: 0in&amp;#34; %)


(% style=&amp;#34;margin-top: 0.14in; margin-bottom: 0in; page-break-inside: avoid; page-break-after: avoid&amp;#34; %)
(% style=&amp;#34;font-family: Calibri; font-size: 1em&amp;#34; %)**Warming is real and anthropogenic—natural variability cannot account for overwhelming trends**

(% style=&amp;#34;margin-bottom: 0in&amp;#34; %)
(% style=&amp;#34;font-family: Calibri; font-size: 0.8em&amp;#34; %)**Schiermeier 11** (Quirin, At least three-quarters of climate change is man-made, December 4th, 2011, http:~/~/www.nature.com.proxy.library.emory.edu/news/at-least-three-quarters-of-climate-change-is-man-made-1.9538)

(% style=&amp;#34;margin-bottom: 0in&amp;#34; %)


(% style=&amp;#34;margin-bottom: 0in&amp;#34; %)
(% style=&amp;#34;font-family: Calibri; font-size: 0.8em; background: rgb(255, 255, 0)&amp;#34; %)__**Natural climate variability is **__(% style=&amp;#34;font-family: Calibri; font-size: 0.8em&amp;#34; %)__**… of changes already being observed**__(% style=&amp;#34;font-family: Calibri; font-size: 0.6em&amp;#34; %).

(% style=&amp;#34;margin-bottom: 0in&amp;#34; %)


(% style=&amp;#34;margin-top: 0.14in; margin-bottom: 0in; page-break-inside: avoid; page-break-after: avoid&amp;#34; %)
(% style=&amp;#34;font-family: Calibri; font-size: 1em&amp;#34; %)**Our tax credit for enhanced oil production stimulates a carbon market and widespread adoption of carbon capture and storage**

(% style=&amp;#34;margin-bottom: 0in&amp;#34; %)
(% style=&amp;#34;font-family: Calibri; font-size: 0.8em&amp;#34; %)**Claussen 12**(% style=&amp;#34;font-family: Calibri; font-size: 0.6em&amp;#34; %)** **– President of the Center for Climate and Energy Solutions [Eileen Claussen (Former Director of the Office of Atmospheric Programs @ EPA and Former Assistant Secretary of State for Oceans and International Environmental and Scientific Affairs), “Speech: Utilizing CCS to Reduce Emissions,” Keynote speech at the 11th Annual Conference on Carbon Capture, Utilization and Sequestration, Pittsburgh, Pennsylvania, May 1, 2012, pg. (% style=&amp;#34;color:#000000;&amp;#34; %)[[(% style=&amp;#34;color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Calibri; font-size: 0.6em&amp;#34; %)http:~~/~~/www.c2es.org/press-center/speech/claussen-carbon-capture-sequestration&amp;#62;&amp;#62;url:http://www.c2es.org/press-center/speech/claussen-carbon-capture-sequestration]](% style=&amp;#34;font-family: Calibri; font-size: 0.6em&amp;#34; %)]

(% style=&amp;#34;margin-bottom: 0in&amp;#34; %)


(% style=&amp;#34;margin-bottom: 0in&amp;#34; %)
(% style=&amp;#34;font-family: Calibri; font-size: 0.6em&amp;#34; %)And (% style=&amp;#34;font-family: Calibri; font-size: 0.8em&amp;#34; %)__I__(% style=&amp;#34;font-family: Calibri; font-size: 0.6em&amp;#34; %) also (% style=&amp;#34;font-family: Calibri; font-size: 0.8em&amp;#34; %)__want to discuss one …carbon capture and sequestration in the future__(% style=&amp;#34;font-family: Calibri; font-size: 0.6em&amp;#34; %).

(% style=&amp;#34;margin-bottom: 0in&amp;#34; %)


(% style=&amp;#34;margin-top: 0.14in; margin-bottom: 0in; page-break-inside: avoid; page-break-after: avoid&amp;#34; %)
(% style=&amp;#34;font-family: Calibri; font-size: 1em&amp;#34; %)**Only CCS can mitigate extreme climate change swings and the worst impacts of warming**

(% style=&amp;#34;margin-bottom: 0in&amp;#34; %)
(% style=&amp;#34;font-family:Calibri;&amp;#34; %)**Der 10** (% style=&amp;#34;font-family: Calibri; font-size: 0.6em&amp;#34; %)- Principal Deputy Assistant Secretary for Fossil Energy @ U.S. Department of Energy [Dr. Victor K. Der (Former Director of the Office of Clean Energy Systems where he directed large-scale demonstration programs, including the Clean Coal Technology Demonstration program, the Power Plant Improvement Initiative, the Clean Coal Power Initiative, and FutureGen, a program for near-zero coal emissions. PhD in Mechanical Engineering from University of Maryland), “ARTICLE: CARBON CAPTURE AND STORAGE: AN OPTION FOR HELPING TO MEET GROWING GLOBAL ENERGY DEMAND WHILE COUNTERING CLIMATE CHANGE,” __University of Richmond Law Review__, March 2010, 44 U. Rich. L. Rev. 937

